imdb.plot outline: Young@Art is a 9-part documentary series about senior citizens who are active in the arts. Some have been practitioners all of their lives, while others decided to pursue their lifelong passion after retirement. Profiles include: a grandma rocker, a ballerina who took up the art form in her 70s, and a tabla player who has recorded with Grammy-winner and world renowned DJ Paul Van Dyk.
